Server monitoring APM event callbacks seem more susceptible than command monitoring events due to the complexity of internal operations involved. There is also the possibility of program termination due to an uncaught exception during client object destruction (e.g. from a commandStartedEvent callback triggered by an endSessions command) triggering the destructor's {{noexcept}} specification.

There are several options to consider:
 # The CXX Driver (and C Driver) documentation must be updated to specify the throwing of exceptions from within an APM event callback as undefined behavior. This describes the status quo.
 # The CXX Driver must be refactored to ensure any exceptions thrown by an APM callback is stored and rethrown only once control flow has returned from libmongoc to mongocxx. This does not seem feasible given the wide scope of potential APM callback invocations: there is no consistent or clear point when the exception should be rethrown.
 # The CXX Driver must break API by adding {{noexcept}} to its APM callback function signatures. In contrast to Option 1, this makes behavior when an exception is thrown well-defined behavior (termination) rather than undefined behavior.

Initially setting the security level of this ticket to "internal" given the unbounded scope of unexpected behavior when an exception is thrown due to failure to run any/all code in libmongoc that is expected to be unconditionally run after the APM callback, which is not limited to deallocations.

The VERSION_CURRENT file used by the CXX Driver may be one of three options per [this block of code|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-cxx-driver/blob/38e6c3ca3609618186110d82d971cf025251865a/CMakeLists.txt#L225] (as of 2023-09-12):
 # None ({{{}BUILD_VERSION{}}} is set).
 # {{${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/VERSION_CURRENT}}
 # {{{}${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/build/VERSION_CURRENT{}}}{{{}{}}}

However, the list of distribution files that are specified as dependencies of the dist target is [hard-coded to unconditionally include|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-cxx-driver/blob/38e6c3ca3609618186110d82d971cf025251865a/CMakeLists.txt#L380] {{build/VERSION_CURRENT}} in the list of files (corresponding to option 2 above).

